      'Global statistical data to understanding life, building empathy, awareness of sustainability helps in change-making!',
      'One important aspect of RealLives is that it can help promote sustainability and the role of young people as change-makers. RealLives demystifies the numbers in statistics and reaches out to young and youth as a real-life experience. This makes statistical data more accessible and relatable, empowering young people to take action in the real world.',
      'RealLives can also be a valuable tool for educators, researchers, and policymakers who seek to understand the impact of policies and interventions on different segments of the population. By using RealLives, they can model and test different scenarios and gain insights into the potential outcomes and impacts. RealLives can also help break down stereotypes and prejudices and promote greater social and cultural awareness.',
      'Moreover, RealLives can help the United Nations Statistical Commission to achieve its vision of putting a face to statistical data. By incorporating human aspects into statistical data analysis, the Commission can provide a more comprehensive picture of the challenges facing humanity. RealLives can help the Commission identify the most vulnerable and marginalized populations and better understand their needs and challenges. This can help the Commission develop targeted policies and interventions that address the root causes of poverty, inequality, and social exclusion.',
      "In today's world which is becoming uncertain and getting divided, India's election to the United Nations Statistical Commission is a significant achievement. By putting a face to statistical data, RealLives can work in collaboration with UNStats to create empathy and understanding among its users and help the Commission develop targeted policies and interventions that address the root causes of poverty, inequality, and social exclusion.",
      'With tools like RealLives, we can better understand and appreciate the diversity of our planet and make more informed decisions that benefit all people, regardless of their background or circumstances.',
